---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';

const S3 = 'https://wf1.s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com';
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="Augmented Reality Toolkit"
  subtitle="Siemens R&D + Google X [2017]"
  description="Hands-free interactive training modules for powerplant engineers. Built on Google Glass, the toolkit allows engineers to access step-by-step maintenance procedures, schematics, and real-time sensor data without ever taking their hands off the equipment."
  role="Product Designer"
  team="Siemens R&D + Google X"
  duration="2017"
  backHref="/digital-work"
  backLabel="Digital Work"
>

  <div class="media-full">
    <video autoplay muted loop playsinline>
      <source src={`${S3}/gl_2.mp4`} type="video/mp4" />
    </video>
  </div>

  <div class="project-body">
    <div class="project-section">
      <h2>Hands-free access to critical information</h2>
      <p>Powerplant engineers require constant access to technical documentation while performing maintenance — a task made impossible when both hands are needed. The AR toolkit surfaces relevant procedures, diagrams, and sensor readings directly in the engineer's field of view via Google Glass.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="project-section">
      <h2>Interaction model</h2>
      <p>The interface was designed around the constraints of a small heads-up display and voice + gesture input. Navigation is minimal, content is contextual, and the system adapts to the engineer's current task and location within the facility.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  .media-full video {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
  }

  .project-body {
    padding: 0 0 60px;
  }

  .project-section {
    padding: 40px 8vw;
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .project-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }

  .project-section p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #444;
  }
</style>
